<subSubSection id="C30175E2FFA7FFB4C6A451EEFE7AFE53" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFA7FFB4C6A451EEFE7AFE53" blockId="19.[151,1437,221,751]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFA7FFB4C6A451EEFE9FFF57" bold="true" box="[151,274,221,247]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male. Body 
<quantity id="4CE38B8CFFA7FFB4C79751EEFDC9FF57" box="[420,580,221,248]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.58" metricValueMax="1.6" metricValueMin="1.56" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" unit="mm" value="1.58" valueMax="1.6" valueMin="1.56">1.56-1.60 mm</quantity>
, yellow to brownish yellow; frons (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFA7FFB4C5E051EEFBB5FF57" box="[979,1080,221,247]" captionStart="FIGURES 13" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1942,1966]" captionTargetBox="[173,1413,918,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-243@18.[173,1413,918,1915]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 13A–F. Pseudacteon setosus Disney et Michailovskaya, male. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. abdominal tergites, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559573" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559573/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Fig. 13A</figureCitation>
) with 10–12 setulae; Lower supra-antennal seta higher than lower fronto-orbital seta; apical seta longer than maximum width of palpus; tarsomere 5 a little swollen at apex and shorter than tarsomere 1, ratio of fore tarsomeres 1.14: 0.74: 0.63: 0.60: 1 (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFA7FFB4C31A5016FA03FE9F" box="[1321,1422,293,319]" captionStart="FIGURES 13" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1942,1966]" captionTargetBox="[173,1413,918,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-243@18.[173,1413,918,1915]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 13A–F. Pseudacteon setosus Disney et Michailovskaya, male. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. abdominal tergites, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559573" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559573/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Fig. 13C</figureCitation>
); setal palisade extends 1/2 (0.55) length of mid tibia (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFA7FFB4C4DB507AFCDDFEC3" box="[744,848,329,355]" captionStart="FIGURES 13" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1942,1966]" captionTargetBox="[173,1413,918,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-243@18.[173,1413,918,1915]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 13A–F. Pseudacteon setosus Disney et Michailovskaya, male. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. abdominal tergites, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559573" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559573/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Fig. 13D</figureCitation>
); setulae below basal half of hind femur only a little differentiated from adjacent setulae of anterior face, and much weaker than those of anteroventral row of outer half (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFA7FFB4C69350A2FE88FE0B" box="[160,261,401,427]" captionStart="FIGURES 13" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1942,1966]" captionTargetBox="[173,1413,918,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-243@18.[173,1413,918,1915]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 13A–F. Pseudacteon setosus Disney et Michailovskaya, male. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. abdominal tergites, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559573" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559573/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Fig. 13E</figureCitation>
); wing (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFA7FFB4C75250A2FE4BFE0B" box="[353,454,401,427]" captionStart="FIGURES 13" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1942,1966]" captionTargetBox="[173,1413,918,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-243@18.[173,1413,918,1915]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 13A–F. Pseudacteon setosus Disney et Michailovskaya, male. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. abdominal tergites, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559573" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559573/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Fig. 13B</figureCitation>
) length 
<quantity id="4CE38B8CFFA7FFB4C41150A2FD04FE0B" box="[546,649,401,427]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.78" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" unit="mm" value="1.78">1.78 mm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity id="4CE38B8CFFA7FFB4C4EF50A2FCCFFE0B" box="[732,834,401,427]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.299999999999999" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" unit="mm" value="0.83">0.83 mm</quantity>
, width/length 0.47; costa index 0.40, costal ratio 1.63: 1, costal cilia 
<quantity id="4CE38B8CFFA7FFB4C7725086FE6AFE6F" box="[321,487,437,463]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" metricValueMax="1.2" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" unit="mm" value="0.11" valueMax="0.12" valueMin="0.1">0.10–0.12 mm</quantity>
; tergite II-VI With very strong setae (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFA7FFB4C5B85086FC63FE6F" box="[907,1006,437,463]" captionStart="FIGURES 13" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1942,1966]" captionTargetBox="[173,1413,918,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-243@18.[173,1413,918,1915]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 13A–F. Pseudacteon setosus Disney et Michailovskaya, male. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. abdominal tergites, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559573" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559573/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Fig. 13F</figureCitation>
), male terminalia brown and anal tube pale yellow at distal two thirds.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
