<subSubSection id="C30175E2FFA7FFB4C6F45382FA0FFD4F" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFA7FFB4C6F45382FA0FFD4F" blockId="19.[151,1437,221,751]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFA7FFB4C6F45382FEB6FD6B" bold="true" box="[199,315,689,715]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Remarks.</emphasis>
This special species is only known from the male sex. It is distinguished from all other species of the genus by the strong setae on the abdominal tergites. Its putative female may be 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B5DEAFFA7FFB4C22253E5FAF3FD4F" authority="Liu et Cai, 2011" authorityName="Liu et Cai" authorityYear="2011" box="[1041,1406,725,751]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Pseudacteon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrisetalis">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFA7FFB4C22253E5FB33FD4F" box="[1041,1214,725,751]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">P. quadrisetalis</emphasis>
Liu 
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFA7FFB4C2C753E5FA85FD4F" box="[1268,1288,726,751]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">et</emphasis>
Cai, 2011
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
